Thanks go to the following people:

@{i}Jan van den Baard @{ui}for GadToolsBox, which was used initially to design
GadMget's GUI.

@{i}Matt Dillon @{ui} for DICE

@{i}Commodore @{ui}for the nifty computer and O/S

@{i}Brian Mury @{ui} for the original AutoFTP script

@{i}Preben Nielsen @{ui} for his help with ListViews

@{i}Paul Vixie @{ui} for the AVL Tree routines

@{i}Mike Gleason, et al @{ui} for ncFTP, and AmiTCP

@{i}David P. Wiles @{ui} for the suggestions and support

...@{i}my friends@{ui}, and all the nice people on the Internet who helped me out
   with Amiga problems.


@endnode


@node AutoFTP

AutoFTP.rexx is an ARexx script designed to completely automate the 
process of downloading files from Aminet via GadMget and ncFTP.

AutoFTP will make use of rexxreqtools.library if it is present, but
does not require it.

In order to make use of AutoFTP, you need to have AmiTCP running,
and ncFTP must be installed on your system.

@{"Setting up AutoFTP" link AutoFTPSetup}

@{"Using AutoFTP" link AutoFTPUse}

@endnode

@node AutoFTPUse

AutoFTP can be run via its icon or the CLI.  (It is a standard
ARexx script)  My favorite way is to run it from a ToolManager
dock ;).

AutoFTP takes one of three possible arguments:

   YES : Cause AutoFTP to always retrieve the newest RECENT file
         before loading GadMget.
         
   NO  : Cause AutoFTP go directly to GadMget without downloading
         the RECENT file or presenting a requester to the user.
         
   DEBUG : Cause AutoFTP to emit information on what commands it
           is executing.
           
You can only specify one of these arguments.  If neither YES nor
NO is specified, a requester will be shown to the user, asking
whether or not they wish to download a new RECENT.

@endnode


@node AutoFTPSetup

In order to successfully run AutoFTP, you will probably need to
alter a few parameters that are embedded within the script.  Use
your text editor to change any values you need to within the
parameters section at the beginning of the AutoFTP.rexx script.
The parameters come set up according to my preferences, which
may not match yours.  A brief rundown of the parameters:

AminetSite : set this to the host name of the Aminet FTP Site you 
             wish to use.

AminetRootDir : set this to the directory path where the Aminet
                archive is based on the FTP server.  The RECENT 
                file should be in this directory on the ftp site.
                
LocalRecentDir : set this to the directory on YOUR system where you
                 wish to keep the RECENT file.
                 
GadMget : set this to the fully qualified filename of GadMget on
          your system.  I.e., you should be able to run GadMget from
          anywhere by typing this line into your shell.
          
ncFTP : set to the fully qualified filename for ncFTP.

GadMgetArgs : If you have any @{"personal preferences" link Startup} for GadMget,
              enter them on this line.  Note that AutoFTP overrides
              certain options, such as AMINETPATH, FILE and OUTPUT, so
              specifying these will have no effect.

DownloadDir : Enter the name of the directory you want AutoFTP to
              place the downloaded files (other than RECENT) into.
      
PreserveSelected : If you set this to YES, AutoFTP will retain any
                   selected filenames from the old RECENT file, putting
                   them in the selected section of the new RECENT file.
                   
DoPruning : If this is set to YES, AutoFTP will check to make sure that
            any item you had in the old RECENT file's selected filenames
            list is not duplicated in the new RECENT file's list of
            filenames.  This option can take some time on slow Amigas,
            or if you had many filenames selected in the old RECENT file.
            
@endnode

@node History "Long long ago.."

( "-" = new feature, "*" = bug fix)
2.05 : (Released 08/05/95)
    * Fixed some problems with iconification.  GadMGet sometimes got confused
      about where its icon was, and wouldn't iconify.  Now it is smarter about
      locating itself, and if it can't find its icon it will iconify with a 
      default tool icon.
    * GadMget was likely to crash if it couldn't reopen its window after 
      iconifying.  Fixed.
    - For files of over 10,000 lines, the "Save" menu option will operate like
      "Save As", bringing up an ASL requester to confirm the save.  I got tired
      of "accidentally" saving INDEX (a 2 minute operation), when I meant to
      select multiple files.
    - @{"AutoFTP" link AutoFTP} is now much smarter about how it saves new RECENT files.
    - @{"CLOSEACTION SAVE" link CloseActionArg}, @{"CLOSEACTION OUTPUT" link CloseActionArg}, @{"CLOSEACTION SAVEOUTPUT" link CloseActionArg}
      and @{"CLOSEACTION NONE" link CloseActionArg} can be specified at once, causing GadMget to save 
      and/or quit when the close box is clicked.
      
2.0 : (Released 07/31/95)
    - Mucked around with the Project menu--Added the @{"Save" link ProjectMenu}, @{"Save As...", link ProjectMenu}, 
      @{"Save & Quit" link ProjectMenu}, and @{"Output & Quit" link ProjectMenu} items.  The "Quit" item now quits 
      without taking any action, and "Output & Quit" does what "Quit" used 
      to do.  
    - Changed many of the keyboard shortcuts around.  Sorry, guys!  :-)
    - Changed the order of the sort types in the menus and with respect
      to the keyboard shortcuts--now they correspond to the column number
      of the data they sort. (FileName = 1, Size = 2, etc.)
    * Fixed a minor misprint in the abort requester.
    - Somewhat faster loading via buffer pairs algorithm.
    - Added @{"LOADBUFFERS" link LoadBuffersArg} option.
    - Added @{"CLOSEACTION" link CloseActionArg} option.
    * Reorganized code structure for file loading and saving.
    - Added @{"Iconify" link ProjectMenu} option to Project Menu, and reworked AppWindow code.
    - Added a counter and an abort sequence for list clearing.
    - Added compilation date to About box.

1.97 : (Released 07/22/95)
    * Fixed window's title bar during "Sort by Age" sorts
    * Implemented the "Sort by Age" tooltypes (oops)
    * The comment lines are now kept at the top of the list
      during Tree Sorts.
    * Fixed several Enforcer hits in the search engine, and an evil bug 
      wherein a search could cause a subsequent ClearList() to hose the system.
    - Rewrote AutoFTP in ARexx, and documented it better.
    - Added @{"COMMENTCHAR" link CommentCharArg} parameter
    - Added @{"OMITCOMMENTS" link OmitCommentArg} parameter
    - Sorts, Loads, Appends, and Searches can all now be aborted by
      pressing <Escape> or clicking on the close box.
    - Removed 'c' directory from GadMget distribution as it is no longer
      needed by AutoFTP.
      
1.95 : (Released 5/28/95)
    - Added file pattern matching to the ASL file requesters, and a FILEPAT 
      startup parameter to set its default.
    - Tree Sorts of large files have been sped up dramatically.  Apparently
      using malloc() and free() is much less efficient than using AllocMem()
      and FreeMem(), so now tree.c uses the latter.  As an example, sorting
      netnet's INDEX by Directory used to take 3 minutes, 28 seconds on my 
      A3000/25, now it takes 48 seconds.
    * "Sort by Age" now works correctly, and line parsing is improved in
      general.
    * Slowed down the progress counters a bit, don't want them to waste CPU.
      (No, this does NOT mean that things are working slower--use a stopwatch
      if you want to be sure ;) )
          
1.9 : (Released 02/10/95)
    * Now (sort of) intelligently parses data lines to find data column
      positions instead of just assuming the data to be in a specific column.
      This should fix problems that occur whenever the Aminet guys decide
      to adjust the column spacings.
    - Added "Sort by Age" function to the sort menu.
    - A space is no longer automatically added between a custom command
      string (i.e. user's "mget" replacement) and the filepath.  This allows
      a bit more flexibility, since you can always add a space in yourself.
    - Added a progress indicator to the Tree Sort function.
      
1.8 : (Released 12/18/94)
    - NewLookMenus flag for proper menu coloring under 3.x
    * Multiple Select/Deselect now smarter/faster for large (de)select ops
      when Keep Sorted is selected. (it was keeping the list sorted at every 
      line transfer, now for large lists it only sorts once, when it's done.)
    * Better handling of out-of-memory situations during file loading
    - Added @{"AMINETPATH" link AminetPathArg} keyword to allow changing of "../.." to something else
    - Added @{"EOL" link EOLarg} keyword for end-of-line string specification
    - Added Clear SubMenu to Project menu, allowing you to clear either the
      files list or the get list.
    * Handles carriage returns at the end of input lines better
    * Killed the occasional Enforcer hit that happened during Case-Insensitive
      Multi[de]Selects.
    * Window title now always properly reset when cancelling a daughter window.

1.7 : (Released 12/02/94)
    * The Search menu is now properly called the Find menu.
    - Added @{"Multiple Select" link findmenu} and @{"Multiple Deselect" link findmenu} options to the Find
      menu.  You can now grab lots of files by key substring!
    - Separated @{"CASESENSITIVE" link casesensitivearg} switch into @{"SORTCASESENSITIVE" link sortcasesensitivearg} and 
      @{"SEARCHCASESENSITIVE" link searchcasesensitivearg} -- although the old switch is still there
      also, and is the same as specifying both of the new ones.
    - Added more keyboard shortcuts  for menu items and switched some around 
      around
    - Added Search from beginning/end, backward search, and Previous
      options to the Find menu.
    - Added {"keyboard shortcuts" link Keys} for moving through the Lists
    * Fixed the "Resizing window causes move to top of list" bug-- thanks to
      Preben Nielsen for help with this one.
    - Sorts by filename now are case sensitive or not depending on Case
      Sensitive flag in Find menu (should this be changed to a separate
      Case Sensitive flag?)
    - GadMget now defaults to a new sort algorithm based on AVL Trees.  This
      means that sorts actually take an acceptable period of time now!  For
      instance, on my A3000/25, sorting wcarchive's INDEX now takes about 35 
      seconds.
    * Fixed a hidden bug that caused the incorrect sort type to be used when
      "Aminet Parse" was reselected with "Keep Sorted" checked.
    - Added an option to switch between the AVL Tree Sort and (old) Bubble
      Sort algorithms, since Tree sorting does take some extra memory and there
      might be people who can't spare the RAM.    
 
1.6 : (Released 10/29/94)
    * Fixed bug that caused text not to be displayed when you didn't
      specify a font to use under AmigaDos 3.0
    - Added the @{"Output To..." link outputto} option to the Output menu.
    - Added the @{"Output Now" link outputnow} option to the Output menu.
    - AutoFTP is now runnable from Workbench via Iconx.
    - AutoFTP no longer requires the s:GadMget.header file.
    - Added the @{"Sort menu" link SortMenu}, with 4 different types of sorts, and the
      Keep Sorted option.
    - Added @{"KEEPFILESORT" link keepfilesortarg} and @{"KEEPGETSORT" link keepgetsortarg} switches
    - Added @{"FILESORT" link filesortarg} and @{"GETSORT" link getsortarg} keywords
      
1.5 : (Released 10/01/94)
    * Fixed bug that would cause nasty crashes if you used a larger font
      on the WorkBench screen and then sized GadMget too small.
    * GadMget now allows you to select files with unknown ('?') file size.
    - GadMget now includes a short AmigaDos script that can be used in 
      conjunction with ncftp to completely automate ftp sessions. 
    - GadMget is now (more or less) font sensitive.
    - Added @{"FONT" link fontarg} and @{"FONTSIZE" link fontsizearg} startup parameters
    - GadMget distribution now also contains EasyReq, a tiny little
      requester-displaying program written by me and used by the
      AutoFTP script.
    * Window no longer has to close and reopen when it is resized (thanks
      to Petter Nilsen for the help on this)
    - Added @{"KEEPBLANKLINES" link keepblanklinesarg} switch
    
1.4 : (Released 08/04/94)
    * Embarrassingly enough, GadMget's output format would apparently 
      only work on a few ftp clients such as ncFtp.  GadMget now also 
      supports a simpler output format that works on all ftp clients.
    - Added @{"NOSIMPLEPATHS" link nosimplepathsarg} switch
    - Added @{"COMMAND" link commandarg} keyword
    - Added @{"NOCD" link nocdarg} switch
    * The NOMGET switch is now called @{"NOCOMMAND" link nocommandarg} (since the generated 
      command is no longer necessarily "mget")
    - Added @{"HEADER" link headerarg} and @{"FOOTER" link footerarg} keywords
    
1.3 : (Released 07/06/94)
    - GadMget now can be started from the WorkBench, with ToolTypes!
    * Removed a glitch which caused GadMget to highlight the wrong line
      if you did a word search on very short files.
    - Added @{"FILE" link filearg} and @{"OUTPUT" link outputarg} parameters
    - GadMget is now an AppWindow if run on the workbench (unless you
       specify @{"NOAPPWINDOW" link noappwindowarg}--another added parameter!)
    - Most errors now pop up EasyRequesters instead of printing to the 
      standard output.
    - GadMget now defaults to opening a screen with the same dimensions as
      the Workbench screen.
    * Removed INTERLACE and OVERSCAN flags since they no longer affect
      anything (see previous item)
    - Funky fresh icon
            
1.2 : (Released 06/25/94)
    - GadMget's window is now resizable
    - Added @{"HEIGHT" link heightarg}, @{"WIDTH" link widtharg}, @{"TOP" link toparg}, @{"LEFT" link leftarg} parameters
    - GadMget can now open on the Workbench or on a Public Screen
    - Added string search window, @{"CASESENSITIVE" link casesensitivearg} parameter
    - Added @{"Output menu" link OutputMenu} to control formatting from within the program
    - Added File Requester
    - Added Busy Pointer
    * Hopefully finally squashed that bug that was causing the occasional
      garbage output
    - AmigaGuide docs!
    - Code is once again a gigantic mess 

1.1 : (Released 06/16/94)
    - Added NOLACE, NOOVERSCAN, @{"LINELENGTH" link linelengtharg}, @{"GETREADMES" link getreadmesarg} , and @{"NOFILES" link nofilesarg}
      parameters.
    * Patched up the source a bit, and spruced up the docs.   
 
1.0 : (Released 06/08/94)
     - First release.  Simple and kind of buggy.
    
@endnode

@node Knownproblems "Known Bugs and Other Problems"

Here are the things that still don't work quite right with GadMget V1.5:
  
- There are still occasional Enforcer hits--unfortunately, they are occasional
  enough to be really hard to pin down!
  
- The NOCD command is probably useless, and doesn't work quite right
  anyway.
      
- Files with tabs and such in them will come out looking rather strange.
  (this isn't a problem if you stick to file listings only, of course)
 
- After reading very large files such as INDEX, GadMget sometimes leaves
  memory rather fragmented.  This is because each line in the file is
  AllocMem'd separately.  
 
- Opening GadMget on the Workbench screen when you don't have Workbench
  loaded causes a 40 byte memory leak.
    
- Using KEEPBLANKLINES together with NOPARSE will often cause GadMget to
  output some extra blank lines at the end of the output stream.

- Probably there are some glitches when using variations of EOL together
  with AminetParse = FALSE, headers, footers?

- If there are different line formats in the listings, sorts will sometimes 
  give incorrect results.  

- GadMget doesn't parse CLI startup args of the form PARAM=value.  It should. 
@endnode

@node Future "What's Next?"
  
- find a fix for the AllocMem/fragmentation problem.

- other bug fixes as they show up (and they will, oh yes, they will... ;-) )

- Smaller & cleaner code

- Add an Iconify gadget.

- Any suggestions?

@endnode 
